Extra:

If the number of -s is greater than -n then -s will become at most -n.

NO negative integer will be accepted, ONLY POSTIVE.

If running with no arguments (e.g "./oss"), default case would be -n 1 -s 1 -t 1 -i 0.1.

Added a header file (shared.h) to store shared data structures and reduce code duplication thus improving readability.

